<p>call "billet."  Everybody has some soldiers to stay with them and they want to eat and smoke and drink and so we try to make things nice for them while they are away from the fighting.  But yes, Monsieur, it was very near to ruin us- this War.  Pardon Monsieur"   And he was gone again.  Still the waggons rolled by outside but I thought of them as going in the other direction two years before full of children, old men and women thrown out from their homes to the mercy of the world, fleeing from the hands of a ruthless nation.  Perhaps-<br/>But here my musing is broken again by the arrival of my pals and we go in to submit ourselves to the cares of Gaston.<br/>Poperinghe<br/>26.9.16<br/>Initials.</p>
